<subSubSection id="02C66578FFFDFFBCFF3D9D4768887C11" pageId="16" pageNumber="30" type="description">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFDFFBCFF3D9D4768587C57" blockId="16.[151,757,259,368]" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">
1926. 
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFFDFFBCFF709D476B8E7C76" authority="CUSHMAN" authorityName="CUSHMAN" box="[218,643,259,280]" class="Globothalamea" family="Verneuilinidae" genus="Gaudryina" kingdom="Chromista" order="Lituolida" pageId="16" pageNumber="30" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="subSpecies" species="leavigata" subSpecies="pyramidata">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFDFFBCFF709D476B147C79" box="[218,537,259,280]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">Gaudryina leavigata pyramidata</emphasis>
CUSHMAN
</taxonomicName>
, p. 587, pl. 16, fig. 8a-b.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFDFFBCFF3D9D7968887C11" blockId="16.[151,757,259,368]" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">
1956. 
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFFDFFBCFF709D796B2E7C33" authority="CUSHMAN." authorityName="CUSHMAN." box="[218,547,317,338]" class="Globothalamea" family="Verneuilinidae" genus="Gaudryina" kingdom="Chromista" order="Lituolida" pageId="16" pageNumber="30" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="pyramidata">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFDFFBCFF709D7968BB7C33" box="[218,438,317,338]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">Gaudryina pyramidata</emphasis>
CUSHMAN.
</taxonomicName>
- SAID &amp; KENAWY, p. 124, pl. 1, fig. 26.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="02C66578FFFDFFBCFF3D9DDD6BDB7FD2" pageId="16" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFDFFBCFF3D9DDD6B8F7CB0" blockId="16.[151,756,409,691]" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFDFFBCFF3D9DDD68057CD0" bold="true" box="[151,264,409,433]" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">Remarks:</emphasis>
The test is somewhat longer than broad and the sutures are distinct and slightly depressed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFDFFBCFF3D9D9D6BDB7FD2" blockId="16.[151,756,409,691]" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFDFFBCFF3D9D9D68C67C90" bold="true" box="[151,459,473,497]" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It is recorded by LE ROY (1953) as occurring in the upper part of his Maastrichtian unit “A” and it was indicated by OSMAN (1954) as an index fossil for the Lower Maastrichtian of the Qabeliat Section. In the study area, it is recorded in the Maastrichtian zones 
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFDFFBCFE329E3F68BB7FD2" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">
(
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFFDFFBCFE359E3F6BFD7FF2" box="[415,752,635,659]" class="Globothalamea" family="Globotruncanidae" genus="Globotruncanella" kingdom="Chromista" order="Rotaliida" pageId="16" pageNumber="30" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="havanensis">Globotruncanella havanensis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFFDFFBCFF3D9EDF68BB7FD2" box="[151,438,667,691]" class="Globothalamea" family="Globotruncanidae" genus="Globotruncana" kingdom="Chromista" order="Rotaliida" pageId="16" pageNumber="30" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="aegyptiaca">Globotruncana aegyptiaca</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFDFFBCFE409ED86BC27FD3" box="[490,719,667,691]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="30">
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFFDFFBCFE409ED86BCB7FD3" authorityName="Zone (CHERIF &amp; ISMAIL" authorityYear="1991" box="[490,710,667,691]" class="Globothalamea" family="Globotruncanidae" genus="Gansserina" kingdom="Chromista" order="Rotaliida" pageId="16" pageNumber="30" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="gansseri">Gansserina gansseri</taxonomicName>
)
</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
